The paper deals with the placement of unmanned aerial vehicle base stations (UAV-BSs) for providing wireless cellular services. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an optimal placement algorithm that utilizes an exhaustive search (ES) and a low-complexity algorithm, which involves optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of robotics (cs.RO), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
